Basic Linux Commands:
---------------------------
date - displays current system date
cal - displays current month calendar
uptime - shows system uptime
users - shows users list
id - shows current user-id, group-id
who - shows username along with public ip
w - shows username, public ip, login in time, idle time, cpu usage

View files:
----------------
ls - list files & directories
cat - view content of file
less - file content page by page
more - file content page by page with percentage
head - default first 10 lines of the file (specify no. of lines as per requirement)
tail - default last 10 lines of the file (specify no. of lines as per requirement)
